                            <comment id="66424" author="jrbman" created="Mon, 16 May 2011 09:05:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a particularly pesky bug to figure out because the problem can be intermittent.  I was passing a URL-encoded UUID from UUID.randomUUID().  Sometimes the UUID would include a / and then fail to map and the problem was far from obvious.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="66472" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Tue, 17 May 2011 01:42:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All HandlerMapping implementations have a setDecodeUrl(boolean) setter that allows you to turn off URL decoding.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="98702" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Mon, 10 Feb 2014 06:26:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Re-opening after more feedback in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-11101&quot; title=&quot;URLs containing %2F (forward slash) are not mapped correctly to @RequestMapping methods&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-11101&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-11101&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Setting decodeUrl=false is not sufficient where the DispatcherServlet is mapped to &quot;/&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="98758" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Mon, 10 Feb 2014 18:13:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking as duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-11101&quot; title=&quot;URLs containing %2F (forward slash) are not mapped correctly to @RequestMapping methods&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-11101&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-11101&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; even though technically this issue was opened earlier. In any case the fix is under &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-11101&quot; title=&quot;URLs containing %2F (forward slash) are not mapped correctly to @RequestMapping methods&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-11101&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-11101&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; targeting version 4.0.2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
